WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:17.330 --> 00:00:20.540
Did you know there's an awesome treasure at the end of this sea?!

3
00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:23.340
And whoever gets it becomes King of the Pirates!

4
00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:24.960
Isn't that exciting?!

5
00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:28.010
Cool new adventures are waiting out there!

6
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:38.060
BON VOYAGE! Light the ember of courage and let the fire grow

7
00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:45.660
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

8
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:48.210
Back when we first started

9
00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:53.430
we had separate ideas about where we would soon go

10
00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:55.380
Things have changed now,

11
00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:00.440
when we look towards our dreams we all share one telescope

12
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:05.680
When you find that your heart's been led astray

13
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.980
time to calibrate your compasses

14
00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:13.010
Set a new course, turn the tables now

15
00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:20.300
BON VOYAGE! Shed your previous baggage, forget the past

16
00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:27.140
Smiles can weather a storm, we know that better than anyone

17
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:29.080
Don't you fret,

18
00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:34.900
tears shed along the way to your dreams are not in vain

19
00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:41.100
You know that you're all PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE

20
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:49.210
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

21
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:53.930
<b>Pirate Zoro vs. Priest Ohm</b>

22
00:01:58.720 --> 00:02:03.060
There are four warrior monks
left in the Upper Ruins.

23
00:02:03.770 --> 00:02:06.310
Since those two
are probably still alive...

24
00:02:06.310 --> 00:02:09.730
that makes four Shandians
and one Blue Sea dweller.

25
00:02:09.730 --> 00:02:12.450
One giant snake and Holy...

26
00:02:14.740 --> 00:02:16.910
That's ten people and two animals.

27
00:02:16.910 --> 00:02:18.660
Ohm, you bastard!

28
00:02:18.660 --> 00:02:21.250
How dare you hurt Wyper?!

29
00:02:21.620 --> 00:02:25.750
Oh? Even though this man is but
a speck in the eyes of God,

30
00:02:25.750 --> 00:02:27.340
he's that important to you?

31
00:02:38.850 --> 00:02:40.100
The end is nigh.

32
00:02:40.100 --> 00:02:41.640
Holy! Now!

33
00:02:56.320 --> 00:02:58.070
Dash, Holy!

34
00:03:16.930 --> 00:03:18.930
What's he up to now?!

35
00:03:18.930 --> 00:03:22.270
Dammit! How can a dog move like
that?! This looks like trouble!

36
00:03:24.390 --> 00:03:28.150
Truly, this is the essence of
the Ordeal of Iron!

37
00:03:28.770 --> 00:03:31.360
The white-barbed death match!

38
00:03:34.990 --> 00:03:39.780
Fence or no fence,
I'm not running away.

39
00:03:40.660 --> 00:03:43.950
You dimwit! It's not just
to stop you from running away!

40
00:03:43.950 --> 00:03:47.120
You're surrounded by the white baarbs!

41
00:03:47.790 --> 00:03:50.000
So what?!

42
00:03:51.290 --> 00:03:52.380
In other words...

43
00:03:58.970 --> 00:04:01.800
touch it, and you'll regret it!

44
00:04:01.800 --> 00:04:04.350
So how do I get out
after I beat you all?!

45
00:04:04.770 --> 00:04:07.690
You can think about that
after you beat us.

46
00:04:09.770 --> 00:04:12.230
Eight people and two animals left!

47
00:04:18.280 --> 00:04:20.320
Wyper!

48
00:04:24.450 --> 00:04:26.580
Thank goodness I found you!

49
00:04:27.460 --> 00:04:28.370
Raki!

50
00:04:28.370 --> 00:04:29.960
Wyper!

51
00:04:29.960 --> 00:04:31.500
Listen to me!

52
00:04:31.500 --> 00:04:34.090
What are you doing here?!

53
00:04:35.090 --> 00:04:38.300
I'm here to relay Kamakiri's warning!

54
00:04:39.430 --> 00:04:42.550
No one... can beat him...!

55
00:04:43.180 --> 00:04:45.060
You have to run, Wyper!

56
00:04:45.060 --> 00:04:46.850
You can't fight him!

57
00:04:55.480 --> 00:04:58.820
Enel is in the forest!

58
00:04:59.400 --> 00:05:00.490
Hey, Raki!

59
00:05:00.490 --> 00:05:04.740
Enel is lightning itself, a force of nature
people have feared as divine for ages!

60
00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:06.990
Stay away!

61
00:05:07.790 --> 00:05:09.290
Get out of here!

62
00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:11.250
We're no match for him!

63
00:05:11.250 --> 00:05:12.880
Hey, stop!

64
00:05:14.090 --> 00:05:14.880
Wyper...?

65
00:05:21.220 --> 00:05:23.390
You called me?

66
00:05:26.600 --> 00:05:27.810
Enel...

67
00:05:27.810 --> 00:05:30.600
Stop it, Enel! Not her!

68
00:05:30.980 --> 00:05:34.110
She abandoned the battle!

69
00:05:34.110 --> 00:05:34.860
Hey!

70
00:05:35.230 --> 00:05:36.190
Raki!

71
00:05:36.190 --> 00:05:37.360
You dummy!

72
00:05:37.360 --> 00:05:40.820
Don't expect to survive
while you're worrying about others!

73
00:05:45.700 --> 00:05:48.120
Raki! Don't fight him!

74
00:05:48.120 --> 00:05:50.580
Run!

75
00:06:02.510 --> 00:06:05.180
He's... invincible...

76
00:06:06.640 --> 00:06:09.140
I got you, Wyper!

77
00:06:15.020 --> 00:06:17.060
You damned idiot.

78
00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:20.900
Y-You have to run...!

79
00:06:45.090 --> 00:06:46.470
Enel!

80
00:06:47.090 --> 00:06:50.890
Huh? That shot didn't work?
Then I'll give you another!

81
00:06:59.360 --> 00:07:02.070
You're softer than I thought.

82
00:07:02.070 --> 00:07:05.280
Wyper, the Shandian warrior!

83
00:07:05.660 --> 00:07:07.740
Woman or not, she's a warrior.

84
00:07:07.740 --> 00:07:11.740
I don't discriminate between the lambs that challenge me.

85
00:07:12.080 --> 00:07:14.210
Do try your best not to die.

86
00:07:36.980 --> 00:07:38.770
So that's...

87
00:07:38.770 --> 00:07:39.980
a god?!

88
00:07:40.440 --> 00:07:42.570
She received divine punishment.

89
00:07:43.280 --> 00:07:46.950
Before I get out of here,
I have to take care of something.

90
00:07:48.200 --> 00:07:49.700
– That giant snake!
– That giant snake!

91
00:07:50.070 --> 00:07:52.160
I've got business with your guts!

92
00:07:53.080 --> 00:07:54.790
Stay out of my way!

93
00:07:57.080 --> 00:07:59.080
Holy! Shake hands!

94
00:08:02.960 --> 00:08:04.380
Eisen Whip!

95
00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:07.590
Axe!

96
00:08:07.630 --> 00:08:08.090
Axe!

97
00:08:20.770 --> 00:08:21.810
Six people...

98
00:08:22.860 --> 00:08:23.940
Two animals...

99
00:08:32.490 --> 00:08:34.120
Ow, ow...

100
00:08:36.580 --> 00:08:38.080
Thank goodness.

101
00:08:42.330 --> 00:08:43.920
Where in the world...?

102
00:08:43.920 --> 00:08:46.010
We were swallowed!

103
00:08:46.670 --> 00:08:48.510
Oh, that's right.

104
00:08:48.510 --> 00:08:51.220
It seems to be quite a long stomach.

105
00:08:51.970 --> 00:08:54.180
Hey, Aisa, are you alright?

106
00:08:54.560 --> 00:08:57.270
W-Wyper, I'm sorry!

107
00:08:58.520 --> 00:08:59.560
Huh?

108
00:09:02.400 --> 00:09:04.110
What is this place?

109
00:09:04.110 --> 00:09:05.860
Inside the snake's stomach.

110
00:09:06.400 --> 00:09:08.030
Pay more attention!

111
00:09:08.030 --> 00:09:09.110
You're so slow.

112
00:09:09.490 --> 00:09:10.490
The snake...?!

113
00:09:10.490 --> 00:09:13.370
Now, let's get out of here
before we're digested.

114
00:09:13.370 --> 00:09:15.580
I wonder if the waver still works.

115
00:09:15.580 --> 00:09:19.080
In any case, why aren't
you on the ship?

116
00:09:19.580 --> 00:09:22.790
The snake chased us,
so we had no choice but to run.

117
00:09:22.790 --> 00:09:25.750
Well, more importantly,
isn't that girl a Shandian?

118
00:09:27.130 --> 00:09:29.090
What the...?! God!

119
00:09:30.260 --> 00:09:31.880
I'll defeat you!

120
00:09:31.880 --> 00:09:33.050
Hey!

121
00:09:33.050 --> 00:09:34.430
Stop it!

122
00:09:34.970 --> 00:09:38.470
By the way, can we break
through this stomach wall?

123
00:09:38.470 --> 00:09:42.600
Are you nuts?! What are we
gonna do if you piss it off?!

124
00:09:42.600 --> 00:09:44.150
Do you wanna die?!

125
00:09:44.150 --> 00:09:45.940
Try to use your head more!

126
00:09:45.940 --> 00:09:48.530
O-Oh, that was a joke.

127
00:09:49.030 --> 00:09:50.440
But really...

128
00:09:50.950 --> 00:09:56.740
if there's someone dumb enough
to piss this snake off, I'd love to meet 'em.

129
00:10:01.660 --> 00:10:04.460
Nami! Weird old man!

130
00:10:04.460 --> 00:10:05.500
You...

131
00:10:06.090 --> 00:10:07.170
Luffy!

132
00:10:07.710 --> 00:10:12.300
What're you doing 
in a mystery cave like this?!

133
00:10:14.300 --> 00:10:16.890
What are you doing
in a place like this?!

134
00:10:16.890 --> 00:10:20.430
I couldn't get out of here.

135
00:10:20.430 --> 00:10:22.180
I can't believe it!

136
00:10:22.180 --> 00:10:24.940
To think that you were
swallowed by the snake too...

137
00:10:24.940 --> 00:10:26.400
What?! Snake?!

138
00:10:26.400 --> 00:10:27.650
That's right.

139
00:10:27.650 --> 00:10:29.360
That's why we're here!

140
00:10:29.360 --> 00:10:33.200
Oh, I see... That must've been rough.

141
00:10:33.200 --> 00:10:35.320
So, you guys were eaten
by a snake, huh?

142
00:10:35.870 --> 00:10:38.620
Like I said...

143
00:10:38.620 --> 00:10:40.290
so were you!

144
00:10:40.290 --> 00:10:43.080
We're inside the snake's stomach!

145
00:10:43.750 --> 00:10:46.540
Don't pull my nose!

146
00:10:47.670 --> 00:10:49.670
That was my Usopp impression!

147
00:10:52.010 --> 00:10:54.220
Who is this idiot?

148
00:10:54.840 --> 00:10:58.680
I hate to say it, 
but he's the captain of our ship.

149
00:11:00.810 --> 00:11:03.430
Oh, so you're the captain?

150
00:11:03.430 --> 00:11:05.770
What is the world coming to?

151
00:11:05.770 --> 00:11:09.270
You must be really slow to not even
notice that you were eaten.

152
00:11:11.070 --> 00:11:13.940
Then we're inside that
giant snake's belly?!

153
00:11:13.940 --> 00:11:15.650
W-Was I eaten, too?!

154
00:11:15.650 --> 00:11:18.030
That's what I've been telling you.

155
00:11:18.030 --> 00:11:20.370
Your clothes are
dissolving, you know!

156
00:11:21.870 --> 00:11:23.830
Whoa! You're right!

157
00:11:23.830 --> 00:11:27.460
Hey, then let's look for
its butthole right away!

158
00:11:27.460 --> 00:11:29.290
Butthole?

159
00:11:29.290 --> 00:11:30.840
Pick a different exit!

160
00:11:31.670 --> 00:11:34.880
We were eaten, so why not
just pop out of its butt?

161
00:11:34.880 --> 00:11:36.880
No! I'd rather be digested!

162
00:11:39.090 --> 00:11:40.260
Nami's scary.

163
00:11:40.260 --> 00:11:43.470
Blue Sea women are brutal.

164
00:11:44.980 --> 00:11:50.980
At any rate, we were eaten because
this snake was in a bad mood.

165
00:11:50.980 --> 00:11:53.440
We should hurry up
and leave before it starts–

166
00:11:53.440 --> 00:11:55.780
The snake's in a bad mood?

167
00:11:58.910 --> 00:12:00.950
– Don't tell me...!
– Don't tell me...!

168
00:12:01.490 --> 00:12:04.580
Were you causing a ruckus
in here all this time?

169
00:12:04.580 --> 00:12:07.580
Yeah, I thought I could
break the wall to get out.

170
00:12:09.420 --> 00:12:12.590
So, uh, this was your doing...

171
00:12:13.340 --> 00:12:16.380
I went a little wild, so I'm hungry now.

172
00:12:16.380 --> 00:12:18.550
Do you have anything to eat?

173
00:12:21.300 --> 00:12:22.390
Wh-What's wrong?

174
00:12:23.560 --> 00:12:26.230
You... are an utter moron!

175
00:13:01.010 --> 00:13:03.470
Crying like a weakling...

176
00:13:03.470 --> 00:13:05.060
That's perfect!

177
00:13:09.520 --> 00:13:12.060
Don't let it digest you, Aisa!

178
00:13:16.440 --> 00:13:18.400
I'll blast its stomach open right now!

179
00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:28.660
You son of a...!

180
00:13:42.180 --> 00:13:44.010
Damn...

181
00:13:44.010 --> 00:13:47.140
That priest's stretchy sword
is really annoying!

182
00:13:47.140 --> 00:13:51.310
I have to take that
snake down first though!

183
00:13:51.310 --> 00:13:54.480
I've gotta get Nami and 
the weird knight out of it right away.

184
00:13:54.480 --> 00:13:58.110
Well, it swallowed them whole,
so I doubt they've died just yet.

185
00:13:59.490 --> 00:14:02.320
But it's just a matter
of time before they do.

186
00:14:02.860 --> 00:14:04.820
Eisen Whip!

187
00:14:05.410 --> 00:14:06.120
Again...!

188
00:14:21.590 --> 00:14:24.220
That bastard... Where is he?!

189
00:14:23.300 --> 00:14:24.220
Eisen Whip!

190
00:14:27.890 --> 00:14:29.850
How does he know where I am?!

191
00:14:30.270 --> 00:14:33.230
It's like he can see through walls!

192
00:14:33.230 --> 00:14:36.520
What's with this spiky-shades freak?!

193
00:14:39.020 --> 00:14:41.570
Die, Blue Sea dweller!

194
00:14:42.900 --> 00:14:45.320
Stop getting in my way!

195
00:14:50.240 --> 00:14:53.040
Another voice has disappeared.

196
00:14:54.750 --> 00:14:57.330
In the Upper Ruins,
there are now only...

197
00:14:57.330 --> 00:14:59.420
five people...

198
00:14:59.920 --> 00:15:00.880
and two animals.

199
00:15:01.960 --> 00:15:02.840
No...

200
00:15:02.840 --> 00:15:04.380
Eisen Whip!

201
00:15:05.130 --> 00:15:06.930
Prepare yourself, Ohm!

202
00:15:06.930 --> 00:15:08.430
Four people and two animals.

203
00:15:13.350 --> 00:15:15.600
Two-Sword Style:

204
00:15:16.940 --> 00:15:17.690
Hawk...

205
00:15:18.060 --> 00:15:19.360
Eisen Back!

206
00:15:19.360 --> 00:15:20.690
...Surge!

207
00:15:21.150 --> 00:15:22.650
Wh-What?!

208
00:15:22.650 --> 00:15:23.860
An iron wall!

209
00:15:24.320 --> 00:15:26.320
This sword is made of iron cloud!

210
00:15:31.330 --> 00:15:34.250
You think clouds have a set shape?

211
00:15:34.250 --> 00:15:35.500
You son of a...!

212
00:15:36.080 --> 00:15:37.540
Eisen Fan!

213
00:15:38.630 --> 00:15:40.040
Eisen Fork!

214
00:15:42.500 --> 00:15:43.960
Eisen Fleuret!

215
00:15:50.260 --> 00:15:51.560
Nothing's working!

216
00:15:51.560 --> 00:15:53.720
I can't get close to him! Why?!

217
00:15:53.720 --> 00:15:55.770
It's like he's predicting
my movements!

218
00:15:55.770 --> 00:15:57.230
What's the matter?!

219
00:15:57.770 --> 00:16:01.230
A swordsman keeping his distance
is an act of futility.

220
00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:03.320
Not quite!

221
00:16:07.820 --> 00:16:09.450
Thirty-Six-Pound...

222
00:16:09.820 --> 00:16:11.780
Phoenix!

223
00:16:12.580 --> 00:16:15.040
Eisen Whip!

224
00:16:18.210 --> 00:16:19.460
It's gonna be repelled!

225
00:16:33.430 --> 00:16:34.390
Dammit!

226
00:16:36.890 --> 00:16:41.480
That's quite an interesting
technique, Blue Sea dweller!

227
00:16:42.310 --> 00:16:45.570
But are you going to try it again?

228
00:16:47.950 --> 00:16:50.450
Hide from my sight all you want.

229
00:16:50.450 --> 00:16:53.990
I can always pinpoint where you are...

230
00:16:56.750 --> 00:16:59.460
by using mantra.

231
00:17:10.010 --> 00:17:12.390
Another one disappeared...

232
00:17:12.390 --> 00:17:15.810
Now three people
and two animals remain...

233
00:17:19.730 --> 00:17:21.310
although...

234
00:17:21.730 --> 00:17:25.020
it'll soon be two people
and two animals.

235
00:17:30.530 --> 00:17:33.490
It seems that you're the top dog
of the Blue Sea group.

236
00:17:34.240 --> 00:17:36.700
You and your comrades
fought valiantly.

237
00:17:38.540 --> 00:17:42.750
However, I've already
taken aim at your heart.

238
00:17:42.750 --> 00:17:46.550
Pray to God, Blue Sea swordsman!

239
00:17:46.550 --> 00:17:48.050
You dumbass!

240
00:17:48.050 --> 00:17:49.510
I'll never...

241
00:17:49.510 --> 00:17:52.090
pray to any god!

242
00:17:52.090 --> 00:17:53.640
How pitiful...

243
00:17:54.300 --> 00:17:55.720
Do as you wish.

244
00:17:56.140 --> 00:17:58.000
I might not be able to see you,

245
00:17:58.000 --> 00:18:01.850
but that extendable sword of yours
will show me where you are!

246
00:18:02.600 --> 00:18:05.310
The moment you find out
will be the moment you die!

247
00:18:05.810 --> 00:18:08.230
The past held thirty-six
worldly desires.

248
00:18:09.480 --> 00:18:11.990
The present holds seventy-two
worldly desires.

249
00:18:12.490 --> 00:18:16.240
The future will hold
one hundred eight worldly desires!

250
00:18:18.290 --> 00:18:21.660
Three-Sword Style:
One-Hundred-Eight-Pound Phoenix!

251
00:18:26.040 --> 00:18:28.250
He dispelled the iron cloud!

252
00:18:55.780 --> 00:18:56.950
Wait!

253
00:19:00.450 --> 00:19:01.660
Huh?

254
00:19:02.160 --> 00:19:04.000
So this dog listens to anyone?!

255
00:19:06.710 --> 00:19:08.920
Knock yourself out!

256
00:19:10.750 --> 00:19:13.220
Now to take care of the snake
and the bazooka guy.

257
00:19:17.010 --> 00:19:19.140
The City of Gold, Shandora...

258
00:19:19.410 --> 00:19:23.020
The golden bell that must've
been in the center of the city...

259
00:19:23.020 --> 00:19:24.600
is no longer here...

260
00:19:25.060 --> 00:19:29.730
The belfry might've housed
a poneglyph engraving as well.

261
00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:37.280
If my suspicion is correct that this city
fell in protection of the poneglyph...

262
00:19:38.070 --> 00:19:40.950
it should still be hidden
somewhere even now...

263
00:19:41.700 --> 00:19:44.540
The belfry housing
the poneglyph engravings...

264
00:19:46.540 --> 00:19:48.250
So then, where is it now?

265
00:19:50.670 --> 00:19:51.880
Oh? This is...

266
00:19:52.630 --> 00:19:54.380
a minecart track.

267
00:19:58.260 --> 00:20:00.600
Something must have been
hauled out of here.

268
00:20:00.600 --> 00:20:02.010
It's newer than the ruins...

269
00:20:02.280 --> 00:20:03.970
What could have been taken...?

270
00:20:06.770 --> 00:20:08.730
Isn't it amazing?

271
00:20:08.730 --> 00:20:12.650
Even after being shot up
to the sky, this city, Shandora,

272
00:20:12.650 --> 00:20:15.030
still exists in all its majesty.

273
00:20:19.070 --> 00:20:22.490
Despite being a legendary city,
it can't be fully admired

274
00:20:22.490 --> 00:20:25.580
if it's covered in clouds.

275
00:20:25.580 --> 00:20:27.660
I'm the one who found it.

276
00:20:29.170 --> 00:20:34.210
My witless predecessors
didn't even notice this grand city.

277
00:20:34.210 --> 00:20:35.170
Who are you?

278
00:20:36.170 --> 00:20:37.630
God.

279
00:20:41.340 --> 00:20:43.680
You're pretty clever.

280
00:20:43.680 --> 00:20:47.140
You must be an archaeologist
from the Blue Sea.

281
00:20:47.140 --> 00:20:53.060
It took us several months
to even find these ruins.

282
00:20:53.060 --> 00:20:58.070
Is it easier to locate when you can
read the symbols on the ruins?

283
00:20:59.780 --> 00:21:03.240
No matter. The gold you seek is gone.

284
00:21:03.240 --> 00:21:05.740
You're a few years too late.

285
00:21:05.740 --> 00:21:07.620
Gold?

286
00:21:07.620 --> 00:21:09.620
Come to think of it, I can't find any.

287
00:21:09.620 --> 00:21:11.580
You must be the one who took it all.

288
00:21:12.380 --> 00:21:14.170
Gold is a marvelous thing.

289
00:21:14.170 --> 00:21:18.720
That glittering metal suits me well.

290
00:21:18.720 --> 00:21:22.090
Then, you took the golden bell
that used to be here, too?

291
00:21:22.930 --> 00:21:24.430
Golden bell?

292
00:21:25.430 --> 00:21:26.890
He doesn't know?!

293
00:21:35.570 --> 00:21:37.070
I'm intrigued.

294
00:21:37.690 --> 00:21:41.150
What did you learn
by reading the symbols?

295
00:21:41.150 --> 00:21:42.360
Nothing...

296
00:21:42.360 --> 00:21:46.160
Unfortunately, if it wasn't here
when you first arrived,

297
00:21:46.160 --> 00:21:49.040
it didn't come to the sky after all.

298
00:21:49.040 --> 00:21:52.670
The huge golden bell
that Shandora took pride in,

299
00:21:52.670 --> 00:21:55.290
and its massive belfry...

300
00:21:55.290 --> 00:21:57.750
I needed to see the belfry.

301
00:21:58.800 --> 00:22:00.920
No, wait... It is!

302
00:22:00.920 --> 00:22:04.340
It's here. It's here in the sky!

303
00:22:04.340 --> 00:22:09.720
When this island was blown
into the sky 400 years ago—

304
00:22:10.350 --> 00:22:15.270
in other words, on the day that
God's Island, Upper Yard, was born—

305
00:22:15.270 --> 00:22:19.030
it's said that a bell chimed loudly
throughout the nation...

306
00:22:20.490 --> 00:22:26.490
The elders call it
"the song of the island."

307
00:22:26.490 --> 00:22:30.700
I see! That bell was made of gold!

308
00:22:30.700 --> 00:22:32.620
Wonderful!

309
00:22:32.620 --> 00:22:34.710
Soon the game will be over.

310
00:22:34.710 --> 00:22:36.790
Eight more minutes to go.

311
00:22:36.790 --> 00:22:41.670
While I'm at it, why don't I look...

312
00:22:42.170 --> 00:22:44.180
for this golden bell?

313
00:22:46.720 --> 00:22:48.930
The golden bell is in the sky?

314
00:22:49.470 --> 00:22:51.600
Then... is the poneglyph here, too?

315
00:22:56.650 --> 00:23:01.440
I sense a maggot
at the edge of the island.

316
00:23:01.440 --> 00:23:02.820
What?

317
00:23:11.870 --> 00:23:13.620
What's the matter, Suu?!

318
00:23:13.620 --> 00:23:15.120
Is it time for your food?

319
00:23:15.120 --> 00:23:17.750
Suu, what's wrong? Are you in pain?

320
00:23:24.300 --> 00:23:26.760
C-Could you be a...?

321
00:23:26.760 --> 00:23:31.680
I'm one of those who fought with
the almighty Gan Fall six years ago.

322
00:23:31.680 --> 00:23:34.020
So as I thought, you're
a member of the Holy Host!

323
00:23:34.810 --> 00:23:38.020
We were kept as captives up there...

324
00:23:39.940 --> 00:23:42.440
What in the world happened?

325
00:23:42.440 --> 00:23:44.570
Conis, attend to him quickly!

326
00:23:44.570 --> 00:23:45.450
Yes, Father!

327
00:23:45.450 --> 00:23:46.700
W-Wait!

328
00:23:48.180 --> 00:23:52.160
My wife and children
are on Angel Island!

329
00:23:52.160 --> 00:23:54.870
Yes, everyone's worried about you all.

330
00:23:55.290 --> 00:23:56.750
Please warn them!

331
00:23:56.750 --> 00:23:58.330
Enel...

332
00:23:58.330 --> 00:24:00.090
plans to return everything!

333
00:24:01.590 --> 00:24:04.300
Skypiea will be dropped
to the Blue Sea!

334
00:24:04.300 --> 00:24:07.050
This nation will disappear!

335
00:24:07.050 --> 00:24:10.260
Th-That can't be...

336
00:24:13.100 --> 00:24:14.770
There's no time to lose!

337
00:24:14.770 --> 00:24:16.940
Tell them right away! Enel is...

338
00:24:19.770 --> 00:24:24.360
planning to eradicate
everyone living in the sky!

339
00:24:28.030 --> 00:24:30.620
Eliminate everyone from the sky?

340
00:24:31.160 --> 00:24:32.910
W-Wait a second, please!

341
00:24:33.540 --> 00:24:37.460
But if he did that, there wouldn't
even be a place for God Enel himself.

342
00:24:38.080 --> 00:24:39.750
He's got an ark!

343
00:24:39.750 --> 00:24:41.170
Ark Maxim!

344
00:24:42.090 --> 00:24:44.460
Ark... Maxim?

345
00:24:45.170 --> 00:24:47.090
What're you...?!

346
00:24:47.170 --> 00:24:48.590
What?!

347
00:24:55.060 --> 00:24:59.560
We were forced to spend the last
six years building that flying ship!

348
00:25:10.510 --> 00:25:15.490
My wish is that, when the sky becomes
peaceful, I'd like to once again

349
00:25:15.490 --> 00:25:20.080
show everyone hospitality
to my heart's content, including you.

350
00:25:27.760 --> 00:25:30.260
Father!

351
00:25:37.430 --> 00:25:39.430
Wh-What did you just do?!

352
00:25:41.190 --> 00:25:42.350
I bestowed mercy.

353
00:25:42.690 --> 00:25:43.610
This man...

354
00:25:44.520 --> 00:25:46.400
has a logia power!

355
00:25:47.440 --> 00:25:51.820
Now, we're running out of time.

356
00:25:52.200 --> 00:25:54.570
Let's settle this, shall we?

357
00:25:54.570 --> 00:25:59.080
My ultimate plan will soon
commence, so...

358
00:25:59.410 --> 00:26:01.830
Ultimate... plan?

359
00:26:04.790 --> 00:26:06.750
God is calling you!

360
00:26:06.750 --> 00:26:10.050
Come to me, lowly beings!

361
00:26:15.850 --> 00:26:17.260
Shango!

362
00:26:24.270 --> 00:26:25.060
What the...?!

363
00:26:37.620 --> 00:26:38.910
What're you...?

364
00:26:41.410 --> 00:26:47.750
I summoned your friends
here... to Shandora!

365
00:26:48.340 --> 00:26:50.510
This man's ability...

366
00:26:50.510 --> 00:26:53.220
What tremendous power!

367
00:27:03.600 --> 00:27:05.440
The ground broke into pieces!

368
00:27:06.190 --> 00:27:07.360
It's Enel!

369
00:27:07.360 --> 00:27:10.610
He's the only one who could
do something like this!

370
00:27:13.190 --> 00:27:14.950
This is bad, I've gotta...

371
00:27:17.070 --> 00:27:18.200
Chopper!

372
00:27:31.550 --> 00:27:32.670
What the hell...?!

373
00:27:32.670 --> 00:27:34.340
There's a hole below!

374
00:27:44.890 --> 00:27:47.310
Let's start the finale!

375
00:27:50.110 --> 00:27:52.530
I shall fly out of here.

376
00:27:52.530 --> 00:27:53.530
Yeah!

377
00:27:53.530 --> 00:27:55.280
There's no end to this!

378
00:27:55.280 --> 00:27:57.780
Luffy! Hold onto the waver!

379
00:27:57.780 --> 00:27:59.620
I'm gonna fire up the engine!

380
00:27:59.620 --> 00:28:02.370
Hey, you! Hold onto me!

381
00:28:02.370 --> 00:28:03.910
Here we go!

382
00:28:06.410 --> 00:28:07.870
I can finally get out!

383
00:28:09.080 --> 00:28:11.840
What?! What are they doing?!

384
00:28:12.250 --> 00:28:13.670
Pierre, go back!

385
00:28:13.670 --> 00:28:15.670
We must save those two!

386
00:28:28.650 --> 00:28:30.230
Hey, wait! We're falling?!

387
00:28:30.810 --> 00:28:32.610
And rather rapidly at that!

388
00:28:32.980 --> 00:28:35.110
Pierre, don't worry about us.

389
00:28:35.110 --> 00:28:37.240
Go help those two inside!

390
00:28:40.620 --> 00:28:44.370
Wh-What about us, weird knight?!
At this rate we'll crash into the ground!

391
00:28:44.370 --> 00:28:48.290
My name is Gan Fall. It's Gan Fall!

392
00:28:48.290 --> 00:28:50.580
Who cares about that right now?!

393
00:28:52.250 --> 00:28:55.800
Crap!
